              <DefinitionShort>a smooth, rounded concretion formed within the shells of certain mollusks and valued as a gem because of its lustrous color (see {D:2.29}).</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>pearl</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In general there is little difficulty involved in obtaining a satisfactory term for ‘pearl,’ since such objects are relatively well known throughout the world. However, in some languages there is no term for ‘pearl,’ and therefore one may use in the case of {S:06602102100030} ‘beautiful white stones,’ and in {S:04000700600020} it may be appropriate to translate ‘do not throw your valuable jewels to pigs.’</Comments>
